nodes.text: Java cake was a type of cake that was edible by humans and Ketzalians. Around 34 ABY, the smuggler Lita shared her java cakes with her colleagues from Ana Tolla's crew, Damar Olin and Izal Garsea, after a mission. Olin consumed the last one, and Lita later commented that it kept him from being fully starved.
Java cake was first mentioned in A Crash of Fate, a 2019 young-adult novel written by Zoraida Córdova.
